  id: Deep_cervicoauricular_muscle.L
  partName: Deep cervicoauricular muscle Left
  descriptionChunks:
  - The left deep cervicoauricular muscle is located within the cervical and auricular
    region of the canine anatomy, connecting deeper neck structures to the ear area.
    This muscle contributes primarily to ear movement and positioning by assisting
    in subtle adjustments of the auricle during communication and environmental awareness.
  - Coordinated ear mobility helps dogs detect sounds accurately and express behavioral
    responses through ear posture. The deep cervicoauricular muscle also works with
    neighboring muscles to stabilize soft tissues surrounding the ear and upper neck.
    Although relatively small, it supports important sensory and communicative functions.
